                    Abstract 
Cybersecurity threats have become increasingly 
sophisticated and frequent, making traditional security 
monitoring and incident response approaches insufficient 
for modern organizations. Security Operations Centers 
(SOCs) are responsible for detecting, analyzing, and 
responding to security incidents; however, manual 
investigation processes often consume significant time and 
resources, resulting in delayed responses and increased 
operational workload. 
This project presents the design and implementation of an 
AI-Powered Security Operations Center (SOC) Automation 
Platform for Windows Environments. The proposed solution 
combines Security Information and Event Management (SIEM), 
Security Orchestration, Automation and Response (SOAR), 
Threat Intelligence, and Artificial Intelligence 
technologies to provide a comprehensive and automated 
security monitoring framework. 
The system utilizes Sysmon to collect detailed endpoint 
activity from Windows machines, including process creation 
events, authentication attempts, and DNS queries. Security 
logs are forwarded using Splunk Universal Forwarder and 
centralized within Splunk Enterprise, where custom 
detection rules continuously monitor for suspicious 
activities such as brute-force attacks, malicious process 
execution, and abnormal DNS behavior.
