Upon detecting a security event, Splunk automatically 
triggers a workflow through n8n, which acts as the 
automation and orchestration engine of the system. The 
workflow extracts relevant indicators of compromise and 
submits them to VirusTotal for threat intelligence 
verification. If the investigated indicator is classified 
as malicious or suspicious, the collected information is  
forwarded to Google Gemini AI, which generates contextual 
security analysis and human-readable threat assessments. 
The final analysis is delivered automatically to security 
analysts through Slack notifications, enabling rapid 
awareness and response to potential threats. This automated 
workflow significantly reduces investigation time, 
minimizes manual effort, and enhances the overall 
efficiency of security operations. 
The developed platform demonstrates how the integration of 
SIEM, SOAR, Threat Intelligence, and Artificial 
Intelligence can improve threat detection accuracy and 
accelerate incident response in Windows environments. The 
project provides a practical and scalable approach for 
modern SOC operations while highlighting the benefits of 
intelligent automation in cybersecurity defense. 
Keywords: Cybersecurity, SOC, SIEM, SOAR, Splunk, Sysmon, 
n8n, VirusTotal, Google Gemini AI, Slack, Threat Detection, 
Incident Response, Security Automation. 
